    "His theory that sculptural traditions traveled like medieval epics and that they were not limited to regional and church authorities brought a storm of contemporary criticism to Porter.": [],
    "His theories were ultimately embraced by later French scholars such as <a href=\"/aubertm\">Marcel Aubert</a>.": [],
    "Porter's championing Spanish art as a key component in the development of the Romanesque, and his arguing against the primacy of archaeology for dating, resulted in a view of eleventh- and twelfth-century art largely adopted today (Seidel, 2000).": [
